# Quality Checks

- After meaningful edits, run a project check (`pnpm build` at minimum).
- Fix lint/type issues introduced by current changes before finishing.
- Do not break existing sections while updating one component.
- Keep behavior intentionally static unless functionality was requested.

# Change Safety

- Do not remove user content or assets unless requested.
- Keep edits scoped to the request; avoid unrelated refactors.
- Prefer small, testable changes and verify after each set of edits.

# Example

```bash
# Standard verification flow
pnpm build
```
